a perfect <HI>Mirroir.</HI> Observe how the <HI>later</HI> is
strongly inforc'd out of the <HI>former.</HI> Since the
<HI>night</HI> of our <HI>sufferings</HI> is now <HI>far spent,</HI> what have
we to do with the <HI>night</HI> of <HI>sin?</HI> And since the
<HI>day</HI> of our <HI>deliverance</HI> is hard <HI>at hand,</HI> what
should we do but<NOTE N="*" PLACE="marg">Vers. 13.</NOTE> <HI>walk honestly as in the day?</HI>
