<HI>dawn; Let us therefore put on the armour of light.</HI>
Let us<NOTE N="*" PLACE="marg">Eph. 5. 8.</NOTE> <HI>walk</HI> in the <HI>light,</HI> as becomes <HI>children of
the light.</HI> Let our <HI>light</HI> so <HI>shine</HI> before <HI>God</HI> and
<PB N="7" REF="10">
<HI>men,</HI> that Men may <HI>see</HI> our good works, and
God <HI>reward</HI> them. That <HI>men</HI> may see our good
works, and glorify <HI>God</HI> in this <HI>present</HI> world;
that <HI>God</HI> may see our good works, and glorify
Us in the world to <HI>come.</HI> Thus we see S. <HI>Pauls
