with a <HI>copulative</HI> [Let us cast off, And let us
put on,] neither of them must go <HI>alone.</HI> We
stand obliged to do them both by indispensable
necessity; nor must we vainly flatter our selves
that Salvation is to be had upon easier terms.
Secondly by the <HI>inforcement</HI> of both <HI>together,</HI>
from the seasonable <HI>conjuncture</HI> of our <HI>affairs.</HI>
For <HI>Because</HI> the Night is far spent, we must <HI>di|vest</HI>
our selves of <HI>darkness;</HI> And <HI>Because</HI> the
