<P>&sect;. 6. For the point of <HI>Infallibility</HI> must needs
be <HI>one</HI> of the two <HI>Pillars,</HI> (whereof the Pope's
pretended <HI>Headship</HI> or <HI>Universal Pastorship</HI> is
the <HI>other,)</HI> wherewith the <HI>Tromperies superstru|cted</HI>
must <HI>stand,</HI> or <HI>fall.</HI> And as it is <HI>skilfully</HI>
contriv'd by the Roman Champions, to spend
their strength in <HI>securing</HI> that <HI>Saving Error, [The
<PB N="402" REF="205">
Church of Rome cannot Err,</HI> because it gives the
the best <HI>security</HI> to whatsoever <HI>other Errors</HI>
their Church can <HI>own;</HI> and under which, as an
<HI>Asylum,</HI> the grossest Follies they can <HI>get-by</HI> do
