Church</HI> was <HI>not-unerrable;</HI> He could not <HI>hin|der</HI>
his own <HI>Discovery,</HI> how very grievously she
had <HI>Err'd.</HI> Nor by consequence could he <HI>hinder</HI>
his own <HI>Conversion</HI> from a Church, still preten|ding
to a <HI>privilege</HI> of <HI>not</HI> being <HI>able</HI> to be <HI>deceiv'd,</HI>
as soon as he found 'twas even <HI>That,</HI> which had
<HI>most</HI> deceiv'd him. And truly had I been tem|pted
