<P>&sect;. 8. For when the <HI>Romanists</HI> contend for the
<HI>Church</HI> of <HI>Rome</HI>'s being <HI>Infallible,</HI> they mean by
the <HI>Roman,</HI> the <HI>whole Church Catholick;</HI> and by
the <HI>whole Church Catholick,</HI> they<NOTE N="*" PLACE="marg"><HI>Father</HI> Iohnson, pag. 350.</NOTE> mean as <HI>many</HI>
as <HI>own</HI> the <HI>Pope</HI> for their <HI>Soveraign Pastor.</HI> This
<PB N="404" REF="206">
is call'd (by a plainer phrase,)<NOTE N="*" PLACE="marg">Father <HI>Cressy,</HI> p. 95.</NOTE> <HI>The present
