there is no better arguing, than to the <HI>Aptitude</HI>
from the <HI>Act.</HI> Nay, in <HI>some</HI> of the 30 <HI>Schisms</HI>
which<NOTE N="a" PLACE="marg">Onuph. <HI>in Chron. p.</HI> 50.</NOTE> <HI>Onuphrius</HI> reckons up in the <HI>Church</HI> of
<HI>Rome,</HI> (before the word <HI>Protestant</HI> was ever
