Does he not think it was an <HI>Error</HI> in the <HI>Council</HI>
<PB N="424" REF="216">
of <HI>Chalcedon,</HI><NOTE PLACE="marg">Concil. Chalced. Act. 15. Can. 28. <HI>Qui Canon <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">enuinus est, non obstante Binii subter|fugio pudendo.</HI> Tom. 3. pag. 446.</NOTE> to Decree unto the <HI>Bishop</HI> of <HI>Con|stantinople,
even in causes Ecclesiastical,</HI> an <HI>equality</HI>
