the Dayes of</HI> Elijah <HI>were</HI> full of trouble&punc; <HI>how
was</HI> Iob <HI>overwhelm'd, and</HI> running over <HI>with his
<PB N="468" REF="238">
Calamity? when the</HI><NOTE N="a" PLACE="marg">Job 6. 4.</NOTE> Terrors of God did set
themselves in aray against him, <HI>how did he</HI><NOTE N="b" PLACE="marg">Vers. 8, 9.</NOTE> long
for destruction? O <HI>(saith<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter"> he)</HI> that I might have
my request, that God would grant me the thing that I
long for! Even that it would please him to destroy
me, that he would let loose his hand, and cut me off.
<HI>How did he</HI><NOTE N="c" PLACE="marg">Job 3. 1, 3, 4, 5, &amp;c.</NOTE> Curse the Day of his Birth, <HI>and</HI> the
Night where in he was conceived? Let that Day be
