brought upon him the</HI> trouble <HI>of being a</HI> Man
born of a Woman: <HI>for we find him complaining
a little after,</HI><NOTE PLACE="marg">Vers. 11. 12.</NOTE> Why died I not from the Womb! why
did I not give up the ghost, when I came out of the
Belly? <HI>And then for the Life of our blessed
Saviour, who is call'd by way of Eminence,</HI>
The Son of Man; <HI>as I observ'd before, that it
was</HI> short, <HI>so must I here put you in mind, it
was</HI> full of Trouble. <HI>He was therefore call'd
